Troubleshooting
===============

   Game reports a file is missing or "Problem with IFF file" or "Can't
open xxx file":

   First of all, you can't install Total Chaos: Battle at the Frontier
of Time on top of an old Total Chaos installation.  It just won't work
for many reasons, sorry about that. :)  Just unarchive the
TotalChaosAGA.lha file into a freshly made virgin directory and
everything will work great.

   Secondly, you absolutely positively CANNOT use lha v2.1!!!!!!!!  lha
v2.1 is totally and completely bugged out!  Delete it immediately!  It
will usually only unarchive around 1000 files out of a 3700 file
archive!  How can you expect to play the game if 2700 of its files are
missing?  Have you deleted lha v2.1 from EVERYWHERE off of your hard
drive?  No?  Stop reading this until you have deleted it.  Go on.  I'll
wait.

   If you get to this part you either were smart enough not to use lha
v2.1 or you have now deleted it. *Whew*, your system is now much more
stable.  Don't you feel better now? :)

   I strongly recommend you to only use lha v1.x.  There are known bugs
in lha v2.2.  v2.2 may or may not unarchive the file correctly.  It
probably will but it might not.  You are 100% guaranteed to succeed if
you use lha v1.x

   Total Chaos has been extensively and continuously tested by many
experienced and some not so experienced :) Amiga users for nearly a
year.  It should provide you with thousands of hours of good clean
monster mashing fun. :)

   Should Total Chaos fail to load it is most likely a simple case of
not enough memory.  Make sure that you have at least 11 megs of free
fastram and at least 512k of free chipram.  If you've got enough ram
but the game won't load then its probably because your memory is
fragmented.  Go to shell and type Avail

   If your largest chunk of fastram is under 5.5 megs then Total Chaos
v4.x just isn't going to be able to load.

   If your largest chunk of chipram is under 400k then the game won't be
able to load either.

   MUI software, like YAM - and especially web browsers - just love to
thrash your memory and fragment it into many small pieces.  Luckily for
you this very easy to fix! :)  Just reset your Amiga and your memory
will be returned to a pristine, fast and unfragmented state.

   Have no fear, Total Chaos does not use MUI.

   Total Chaos only uses AmigaOS.  Total Chaos does not use MUI OS, P96
OS, CyberGraphX OS, Linux OS, Mac OS, Palm OS, Bill Gates OS nor any
other OS that you can think of.

   Why are the sounds out of Sync?

